    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to observe the massive star forming clusters NGC 6334I &amp; I(N) in the highest angular resolution
with ALMA in band 7. So far, ALMA will provide the highest resolution observation of these sources and
the dust continuum maps from it, with an estimated sensitivity of at least ten times better than in previous
observations, will give us access to much lower mass cluster members. We aim at deep continuum images
to provide us with a more complete census of all cores in order to derive the clump mass function, although
the brightest hot core will probably limit the dynamic range. Line observations of HCN, CO, CS and their
isotopologues will trace infall and outflow motions at different optical depths. The observations will help
us to determine how the global infall onto the cluster is divided between the cluster members under the
influence of accretion and feedback mechanisms, and will be compared in detail with models of 3D-radiative
transfer codes.</prp:abstract>
